# Session Information Protocol

## Session Start Announcement

At the beginning of **each new chat session**, provide a short summary of active context:

### 1. Available Skills

List skills under `.agents/skills/` with:
- Skill name
- Brief description (from frontmatter)
- When to use it

Example:

```
📚 Skills available in this project:
• writing-plans: Create detailed implementation plans
• executing-plans: Execute plans step by step
• to-prd: Turn conversations into structured PRDs
• verification-before-completion: Verify work before claiming done
• python-testing-patterns: Pytest testing patterns
```

### 2. Active Rules

List rules in `.cursor/rules/` with:
- Rule name
- Description
- Scope (always apply or file-specific)

Example:

```
📋 Active rules:
• session-info (always): Session skills/rules summary
• python-standards (*.py): Python code standards
• home-assistant-integration (custom_components): HA integration conventions
```

### 3. RTK Status

State whether RTK is available and active for token optimization:

```
⚡ RTK: [Active / Not detected]
RTK can reduce token usage by 60–90% by rewriting shell commands.
```

## When to Announce

- At the start of each new chat session
- When the user asks what skills or rules are available
- Do **not** announce mid-task unless it is relevant

## Announcement Format

```markdown
---
🤖 Session info

📚 **Skills available:** [count] skills
📋 **Active rules:** [count] rules
⚡ **RTK:** [status]

Say "list skills" or "show rules" for details.
---
```

## Important

- Keep the announcement concise (about 3–5 lines)
- Do not read every file each session (use cached knowledge)
- Expand details only if the user asks
